-- =============================================================
-- Circuit  : Wide AND Tree
-- File     : wide_and_tree.vhd
--
-- WHAT THIS CIRCUIT DOES:
--   Contains 128 independent AND gates.
--   Each gate: Yi <= Ai and Bi  (i = 0 to 127)
--   No gate reads another gate's output — all 128 are completely
--   independent of each other.
--
-- WHY THIS MATTERS FOR PARALLELISM:
--   All 128 gates land in Layer 0 of the dependency graph.
--   With 4 threads: each thread handles 32 gates simultaneously.
--   This is the BEST CASE for parallelism — one fat layer,
--   zero inter-layer transitions, maximum parallel throughput.
--   Expected speedup: ~4x on 4 threads for the execution phase.
--
-- DEPENDENCY GRAPH:
--   Layer 0: 128 AND gates (all independent, run in parallel)
--
-- SIGNALS:
--   A0..A127 : first input to each AND gate
--   B0..B127 : second input to each AND gate
--   Y0..Y127 : output of each AND gate
--   Total: 384 signals, 128 gates
--
-- STIMULUS — 4 test vectors (10 ns each):
--   t=0  : A=0, B=0  -> all Y=0  (0 AND 0 = 0)
--   t=10 : A=1, B=0  -> all Y=0  (1 AND 0 = 0)
--   t=20 : A=1, B=1  -> all Y=1  (1 AND 1 = 1, all 128 outputs flip)
--   t=30 : A=0, B=1  -> all Y=0  (0 AND 1 = 0)
--
-- HOW TO BENCHMARK:
--   OMP_NUM_THREADS=1 ./simulator test_vhdl/large/wide_and_tree.vhd t1.vcd
--   OMP_NUM_THREADS=4 ./simulator test_vhdl/large/wide_and_tree.vhd t4.vcd
--   diff t1.vcd t4.vcd   <-- must be empty (bit-identical output)
-- =============================================================

